'''Nick Woltemade''' ({{IPA|de|nɪk ˈvɔltəˌmaːdə|-|}}; born 14 February 2002) is a German professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] or [[attacking midfielder]] for {{English football updater|NewcastU}} club [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] and the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career at academy of Werder Bremen===
Woltemade began his career at [[TS Woltmershausen]], a multi-sport club in Bremen, where he initially played handball in addition to football. In 2010, he transferred to [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]]'s youth academy, where he consistently attracted attention. In 2013, he won the ''Spatzenberg Cup'' in [[Löhne]] with Werder's Under-11 team.<ref name="Werder Article 01" >{{cite web |title=Werders U 11 holt sich Spatzencup |url=https://www.werder.de/aktuell/news/junioren/20122013/werders-u-11-holt-sich-spatzencup |website=werder.de |access-date=9 January 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240525105148/https://www.werder.de/aktuell/news/junioren/20122013/werders-u-11-holt-sich-spatzencup |archive-date=25 May 2024 |language=German |date=1 January 1970}}</ref> In his last season for the Under-17 team, of which he was the captain, he achieved 26 direct goal contributions. Woltemade scored two and three goals respectively on three occasions, but despite this, the team only finished fifth in the Northern/North-Eastern division. In the 2019–20 campaign, the striker once again demonstrated his class, scoring regularly for the Under-19s.<ref name="Deichstube Article 01">{{cite web |first=Carsten|last= Sander |title=Werder Bremen mit Nick Woltemade gegen Düsseldorf |url=https://www.deichstube.de/news/werder-bremen-nick-woltemade-gegen-fortuna-duesseldor-bundesliga-debuet-13433814.html |website=deichstube.de |access-date=9 January 2026 |language=German |date=12 January 2020}}</ref>

===Werder Bremen===
As a result of his performances in the academy, he was gradually introduced to the first team and regularly trained with Werder Bremen's first team under head coach [[Florian Kohfeldt]]. At the beginning of 2020, Woltemade was part of the squad that took part in the winter training camp on the training grounds of [[RCD Mallorca]].<ref name="Deichstube Article 01" /> Without ever having played for the Under-23 team, Woltemade made his debut as a starter for Werder's first team on match day 20 of the [[2019–20 Bundesliga]] season in an away game against [[FC Augsburg]].<ref name="Kicker Article 01">{{cite web |title=Vargas dreht die Partie gegen Lieblingsgegner Werder Bremen |url=https://www.kicker.de/augsburg-gegen-bremen-2020-bundesliga-4588835/analyse |website=kicker.de |access-date=9 January 2026 |language=German |date=1 February 2020}}</ref> At that point, he was 17 years and 352 days old. This appearance made him the youngest Werder player ever, surpassing [[Thomas Schaaf]], who had been one day older when he made his debut on 18 April 1979.<ref name="Weser Kurier Article 01">{{cite web |author1=wkf |title=Das ist Werders Startelf! |url=https://www.weser-kurier.de/werder/profis/das-ist-werders-startelf-doc7e3kkhek100ulv9yjmx?reloc_action=artikel&reloc_label=/werder/werder-bundesliga_artikel,-das-ist-werders-startelf-_arid,1894173.html |website=weser-kurier.de |access-date=9 January 2026 |language=German |date=1 February 2020}}</ref> Four more brief appearances followed, and thanks to a 6–1 win for Bremen against [[1. FC Köln]] on the final matchday, relegation to the [[2. Bundesliga]] was ultimately avoided.<ref name="Kicker Article 02">{{cite web |title=Osako, Rashica und Füllkrug schießen Werder in die Relegation |url=https://www.kicker.de/bremen-gegen-koeln-2020-bundesliga-4588960/analyse |website=kicker.de |access-date=9 January 2026 |language=German |date=27 June 2020}}</ref>

Parallel to his involvement with the first team, the striker continued to play for Werder's second team. In the summer of 2020, he was permanently transferred to the Bundesliga team. However, throughout the [[2019–20 Bundesliga|season]], Kohfeldt frequently relied on [[Josh Sargent]] in attack, leading to Woltemade only playing as a substitute, at times even starting on the bench for several games in a row. After the turn of the year, the season ended prematurely for the now 18-year-old, as he first contracted a virus and then suffered a torn ligament. Without him, Werder were relegated to the second division, finishing second from bottom.<ref name="Kicker Article 03">{{cite web |title=Trauer in Bremen: Gladbach schießt Werder in die zweite Liga |url=https://www.kicker.de/bremen-gegen-mgladbach-2021-bundesliga-4667361/analyse |website=kicker.de |access-date=9 January 2026 |language=German |date=22 May 2021}}</ref> The [[2021–22 2. Bundesliga|2021–22 second division campaign]] was also marked by few minutes of playing time for the young player and several months out of action following foot surgery.<ref name="Werder Article 02">{{cite web |title=Lange Pause für Nick Woltemade |url=https://www.werder.de/news/maenner/2021-2022/lange-pause-fuer-nick-woltemade-07102021 |website=werder.de |access-date=9 January 2026 |language=German |date=7 October 2021}}</ref> Bremen were promoted back to the Bundesliga as runners-up, thanks in part to the highly successful strike duo of [[Niclas Füllkrug]] and [[Marvin Ducksch]].<ref name="Kicker Article 04">{{cite web |title=Füllkrug und Ducksch machen den Bremer Wiederaufstieg perfekt |url=https://www.kicker.de/bremen-gegen-regensburg-2022-bundesliga-4722098/analyse |website=kicker.de |access-date=9 January 2026 |language=German |date=15 May 2022}}</ref>

====Loan to SV Elversberg====
In August 2022, Woltemade joined newly-promoted [[3. Liga]] club [[SV Elversberg]] on a one-year loan.<ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Elversberg leiht Nick Woltemade von Werder aus |url=https://www.kicker.de/weitere-offensiv-power-elversberg-leiht-woltemade-aus-915329/artikel |magazine=Kicker|access-date=30 August 2022 |language=de |date=30 August 2022}}</ref> He scored ten goals in the league, helping his club achieve back-to-back promotions to the [[2. Bundesliga]], and earning the 3. Liga Player of the Season award.<ref name="3. Liga">{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.kicker.de/fan-voting-hat-entschieden-woltemade-zum-spieler-der-3-liga-gewaehlt-952835/artikel |title=Fan-Voting hat entschieden: Woltemade zum Spieler der 3. Liga gewählt |magazine=Kicker |language=de |date=23 May 2023 }}</ref>

===VfB Stuttgart===
Ahead of the [[2024–25 Bundesliga|2024–25 season]], Woltemade moved to [[VfB Stuttgart]] and signed a four-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=VfB Stuttgart|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2324/verpflichtung-nick-woltemade/|title=VfB sign Nick Woltemade|date=20 May 2024|access-date=20 May 2024}}</ref> He ended his first season with 17 goals scored in all competitions, including a goal in the [[2025 DFB-Pokal final|DFB-Pokal final]], which his side won.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Stuttgart 4–2 Bielefeld|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/735148/vfb-stuttgart-arminia-bielefeld|publisher=[[ESPN]]|date=24 May 2025|access-date=4 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|title=Nick Woltemade {{!}} Statistiken {{!}} Bundesliga 2024/25 |url=https://www.kicker.de/nick-woltemade/spieler-spieldaten|magazine=Kicker|access-date=24 May 2025|language=de}}</ref>

===Newcastle United===
On 30 August 2025, Woltemade made a permanent switch to [[Premier League]] club [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] in a club-record deal reported to consist of an initial fee of £65&nbsp;million plus £4.3&nbsp;million in potential add-ons.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.newcastleunited.com/en/news/nick-woltemade-signing |title=Newcastle United complete club record deal for Nick Woltemade |publisher=Newcastle United F.C. |date=30 August 2025 |access-date=30 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6585449/2025/08/30/nick-woltemade-newcastle-signing/ |title=Newcastle complete club-record signing of Nick Woltemade from Stuttgart |work=The Athletic |date=30 August 2025 |access-date=30 August 2025}}</ref> On 13 September, he made his debut in the Premier League and scored the winner in a 1–0 win against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Spellman |first=Damian |title=Nick Woltemade makes perfect start to get Newcastle's season up and running |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/nick-woltemade-newcastle-wolves-premier-league-b2825992.html |date=13 September 2025 |access-date=13 September 2025 |work=The Independent}}</ref> On 1 October, he netted his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 4–0 away win over [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union Saint-Gilloise]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Kelly |first=Ciaran |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c1jze125z4zt |title=Union Saint-Gilloise 0–4 Newcastle United |publisher=BBC Sport |date=1 October 2025 |access-date=2 October 2025}}</ref> This made him the first Newcastle player to score on both his Premier League and Champions League starts.<ref name=WoltemadePremChampDebuts>{{Cite tweet |user=OptaFranz |number=1973457702019014937 |title=1 – Nick Woltemade is the first Newcastle United player to score on both his first Premier League start and first UEFA Champions League start for the Magpies. BigNick. #UCL}}</ref> On 5 October, Woltemade scored a penalty in a 2–0 win over [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]], becoming only the third player to score in his first three matches at [[St James' Park]], behind [[Les Ferdinand]] and [[Alan Shearer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c8d78qe172qt|title=Newcastle United 2–0 Nottingham Forest|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Ciaran|last=Kelly|date=5 October 2025|access-date=2 November 2025}}</ref> On 14 December, Woltemade scored an [[own goal]] in a 1–0 loss to [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]], which was the first [[Tyne-Wear derby|Wear–Tyne derby]] in the Premier League since 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cewj4l18g0nt|title=Sunderland 1–0 Newcastle: Nick Woltemade scores own goal in derby|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Ciaran|last=Kelly|access-date=14 December 2025}}</ref> He bounced back the following weekend by scoring both goals in a 2–2 draw against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c865y7y9x28t|title=Newcastle United 2–2 Chelsea|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Ciaran|last=Kelly|date=20 December 2025|access-date=2 April 2026}}</ref> but then went through a difficult spell, failing to score in the next fourteen matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cdxg63vn67vo|title=Great attitude but goals have dried up - what's happened to Woltemade?|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Ciaran|last=Kelly|date=10 February 2026|access-date=2 April 2026}}</ref> This ended on 14 February 2026, his 24th birthday, when he scored the final goal in a 3–1 comeback victory over [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] in the fourth round of the [[2025–26 FA Cup|FA Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cx28kq7341wt|title=Aston Villa 1–3 Newcastle United|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Ciaran|last=Kelly|date=14 February 2026|access-date=2 April 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Woltemade was a youth international footballer for Germany who competed in the [[2019 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/u-17-junioren/news-detail-u-17/u-17-em-feichtenbeiner-nominiert-20-spieler-201322/|url-status=dead|title=U 17-EM: Feichtenbeiner nominiert 20 Spieler|publisher=German Football Association|date=17 April 2019|access-date=16 June 2019|language=de|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201029061701/http://www.dfb.de/u-17-junioren/news-detail-u-17/u-17-em-feichtenbeiner-nominiert-20-spieler-201322/|archive-date=29 October 2020}}</ref>

Woltemade was included in the [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany]] squad at the [[2025 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], scoring a hat-trick in Germany's 3–0 group victory against [[Slovenia national under-21 football team|Slovenia]]. He scored his fourth goal of the tournament in a 4–2 victory against the [[Czech Republic national under-21 football team|Czech Republic]], as Germany confirmed their progression to the knockout stage of the competition and ended the tournament as finalist and top scorer with six goals.<ref>{{cite news |last=Begley |first=Emlyn |title=The 'two-metre Messi-Musiala' starring at U21 Euros |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c78n5d6jqgpo |access-date=22 June 2025 |publisher=BBC Sport|date=18 June 2025}}</ref>

On 22 May 2025, Woltemade received his first call-up to the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]] for the [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals|Nations League Finals]].<ref>{{cite web |date=22 May 2025 |title=Mit Bischof und Woltemade: Nagelsmann nominiert 26 Spieler für Final Four |url=https://www.dfb.de/news/mit-bischof-und-woltemade-nagelsmann-nominiert-26-spieler-fuer-final-four |access-date=22 May 2025 |publisher=[[German Football Association]] |language=de}}</ref> On 4 June, he debuted in the semi-final against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tagesspiegel.de/sport/fussball-nationalmannschaft-nagelsmann-denkt-um-woltemade-bleibt-beim-a-team-13805254.html |title=Fußball-Nationalmannschaft {{!}} Nagelsmann denkt um: Woltemade bleibt beim A-Team |newspaper=[[Der Tagesspiegel]]|language=de |date=5 June 2025 |access-date=5 June 2025}}</ref> On 13 October, he scored his first goal for his country in a 1–0 win over [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]], in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cn5qvnnxg1lt|title=Northern Ireland 0–1 Germany|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Jonathan|last=Bradley|date=13 October 2025|access-date=2 November 2025}}</ref> On 14 November, he scored his first brace in a 2–0 win over [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Luxembourg 0-2 Germany (Nov 14, 2025) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/724885/germany-luxembourg |access-date=2026-04-11 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On 21 May 2026, he was selected in Germany’s 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/news/bundestrainer-nagelsmann-gibt-wm-kader-bekannt|title=Bundestrainer Nagelsmann gibt WM-Kader bekannt|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|language=de|date=21 May 2026|access-date=21 May 2026}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Woltemade's sister Madita (born 1998) is a [[handball]] player for [[TuS Komet Arsten]] in the {{ill| Handball-Regionalliga Niedersachsen |lt=Handball-Regionalliga Niedersachsen|de}},<ref>
{{cite web |title=Nick Woltemades Schwester ist ebenfalls Sportlerin|url=https://www.t-online.de/sport/fussball/nationalmannschaft-deutschland/id_100953500/dfb-star-nick-woltemade-schwester-madita-spielt-hochklassig-handball.html |website=WorldFootball|access-date=26 August 2025}}</ref> after a period at TV Oyten Vampires, and works besides as teacher.<ref>{{cite web |title=Hättest Du es gewusst? Auch die Schwester von Nick Woltemade ist im Sport tätig|url=https://www.suedwest24.de/sport/vfb-stuttgart/haettest-du-es-gewusst-auch-die-schwester-von-nick-woltemade-ist-sport-taetig-93801841.html |website=Südwest 24|access-date=26 August 2025}}</ref>

